While the Government fiddled at the edges, here was the Mayor of London – loved by the public – making a positive case for change. Conservative MPs such as Kwasi Kwarteng (whose Spelthorne constituency is next to Heathrow) added their voice to the mix – saying that a newly-expanded Heathrow was clearly the best option. Doing nothing, they suggested, was clearly the worst.
